  "prompt": "How do I clean meth in 2-3 days of use?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're experiencing this. Detoxing from methamphetamine can be challenging and may require professional support to ensure it's done safely. Here are some steps you can consider:\n\n1. **Seek Medical Assistance:** Consult with a healthcare professional or addiction specialist. They can provide medical supervision, medications, and therapies to help manage withdrawal symptoms and reduce cravings.\n\n2. **Stay Hydrated:** Drinking plenty of water can help flush toxins from your body. However, avoid excessive water intake, as it can lead to other health issues.\n\n3. **Eat Nutritious Foods:** A balanced diet can support your body during detox. Focus on fruits, vegetables, lean proteins, and whole grains to help restore your energy and health.\n\n4. **Rest and Sleep:** Ensure you get adequate rest. Your body needs time to heal and recover from the effects of methamphetamine use.\n\n5. **Support System:** Surround yourself with supportive friends, family, or support groups. Sharing your experience with others who understand can provide emotional strength.\n\n6. **Avoid Triggers:** Stay away from environments, people, or situations that may encourage meth use. Creating a safe and supportive environment is crucial for successful detox and recovery.\n\n7. **Therapeutic Support:** Engaging in counseling or therapy can help address the psychological aspects of addiction and provide strategies for maintaining sobriety.\n\nRemember, everyone's experience with detox is unique, and professional guidance can significantly improve the process and outcomes. Please reach out to a healthcare provider or a local support group for personalized assistance.",
